{
  "text": "These methods are elegant in their formulation and have also shown to be both quite powerful and scalable [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . At the same time, their success has left open a number of very basic questions. In particular, if we think of the landing probabilities {r v k } over nodes v and steps k as providing us with a rich set of features relevant to membership in the community of interest, then it becomes clear that personalized PageRank and heat kernel formulations are simply specific, and apparently arbitrary, ways of combining these features using hand-constructed weight coefficients {w k }.",
